Template: send-to-influx/sources-to-configure
Type: multiselect
Choices: hue, zappi, harvi, eddi, octopus, openmeteo, carbonintensity, speedtest
Default:
Description: Which data sources do you want to configure now?
 You can leave this empty and edit /etc/send-to-influx/settings.yaml by hand
 later, or run 'dpkg-reconfigure send-to-influx' at any time to change this.
 Only the fields needed to actually reach each source's API are asked here -
 tuning settings (intervals, timeouts, which fields to collect) keep their
 shipped defaults and can be adjusted in settings.yaml afterwards.

Template: send-to-influx/influx-url
Type: string
Default:
Description: InfluxDB URL (leave blank for a local instance)
 The base URL of your InfluxDB server, e.g. https://influx.example.com:8086.
 Leave this blank to default to http://localhost:8086.
 When reconfiguring an install whose InfluxDB credentials are already stored
 in systemd-creds, a blank URL keeps the currently configured one - enter
 http://localhost:8086 explicitly to point it back at a local instance.

Template: send-to-influx/influx-identity
Type: string
Default:
Description: InfluxDB user (v1) or organisation (v2)
 For InfluxDB v1 (username/password authentication) enter the username. For
 InfluxDB v2 (token authentication) enter the organisation name. Which one
 applies is detected automatically once the server is reachable - you don't
 need to know your InfluxDB version to answer this.
 When reconfiguring, leaving this blank keeps the currently configured value.

Template: send-to-influx/influx-secret
Type: password
Description: InfluxDB password (v1) or API token (v2)
 For InfluxDB v1 enter the password. For InfluxDB v2 enter the API token.
 When reconfiguring, leaving this blank keeps the credential already stored
 in systemd-creds, if any (a secret kept in plaintext in settings.yaml is
 not read back here).

Template: send-to-influx/hue-host
Type: string
Default:
Description: Hue bridge hostname or IP address

Template: send-to-influx/hue-user
Type: password
Description: Hue bridge username/API key
 See https://developers.meethue.com/develop/get-started-2/ for how to
 generate this.
 When reconfiguring, leaving this blank keeps the credential already stored
 in systemd-creds, if any (a secret kept in plaintext in settings.yaml is
 not read back here).

Template: send-to-influx/hue-temperature-units
Type: select
Choices: C, F
Default: C
Description: Temperature units for Hue sensor readings
 Pre-filled from your system locale where possible, but always worth
 double-checking.

Template: send-to-influx/myenergi-apikey
Type: password
Description: MyEnergi API key
 Shared across Zappi/Eddi/Harvi devices - asked once regardless of how many
 of those you selected.
 When reconfiguring, leaving this blank keeps the credential already stored
 in systemd-creds, if any (a secret kept in plaintext in settings.yaml is
 not read back here).

Template: send-to-influx/zappi-serial
Type: string
Default:
Description: Zappi device serial number

Template: send-to-influx/harvi-serial
Type: string
Default:
Description: Harvi device serial number

Template: send-to-influx/eddi-serial
Type: string
Default:
Description: Eddi device serial number

Template: send-to-influx/octopus-api-key
Type: password
Description: Octopus Energy API key
 From https://octopus.energy/dashboard/developer/
 When reconfiguring, leaving this blank keeps the credential already stored
 in systemd-creds, if any (a secret kept in plaintext in settings.yaml is
 not read back here).

Template: send-to-influx/octopus-mpan
Type: string
Default:
Description: Octopus Energy electricity meter MPAN
 The 13-digit MPAN number found on your bill.

Template: send-to-influx/octopus-meter-serial
Type: string
Default:
Description: Octopus Energy electricity meter serial number
 Found on your bill or on the meter itself.

Template: send-to-influx/openmeteo-latitude
Type: string
Default:
Description: Latitude for Open-Meteo weather data

Template: send-to-influx/openmeteo-longitude
Type: string
Default:
Description: Longitude for Open-Meteo weather data
